
# Acceptable .md File Types in ~/.config/Code/User/prompts/ (Copilot/Agent System)

## 1. `.instructions.md`
**Purpose:** Instruction set, auto-applied by file pattern.
**Front-matter (YAML) options:**
- `name` (string): Human-readable name.
- `applyTo` (string): Glob pattern for file matching (**required**).
- `description` (string, optional): Short summary.
- Any other fields are ignored.

## 2. `.skill.md`
**Purpose:** Defines a skill, invokable via `/skill-name`.
**Front-matter options:**
- `name` (string): Skill name (**required**).
- `kind` (string): Must be "skill" (**required**).
- `category` (string, optional): Category label.
- `summary` (string, optional): Short summary.
- `description` (string, optional): Detailed description.
- Any other fields are ignored.

## 3. `.agent.md`
**Purpose:** Defines an agent, invokable via `/agent-name`.
**Front-matter options:**
- `name` (string): Agent name (**required**).
- `description` (string): Agent summary (**required**).
- Any other fields are ignored.

## 4. `.prompt.md`
**Purpose:** Prompt template for agent/skill behavior.
**Front-matter options:**
- `name` (string, optional): Prompt name.
- `description` (string, optional): Prompt summary.
- Any other fields are ignored.

## 5. Documentation Files (`README.md`, `AGENTS.md`, etc.)
**Purpose:** Human-readable documentation only.
**Front-matter:** Not required or used.
